WEBVTT

p01
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.114
Sooner or later a migrated client says the platform looks different,

p02
00:00:03.114 --> 00:00:05.379
or asks where one of their features went.

p03
00:00:05.379 --> 00:00:08.697
You have two kinds of answer, and one hard rule.

p04
00:00:08.697 --> 00:00:09.920
Here they are.

p05
00:00:10.353 --> 00:00:14.627
Start with the big picture, and attribute it.

p06
00:00:14.627 --> 00:00:16.218
Per Micrologic platform documentation,

p07
00:00:16.218 --> 00:00:20.593
all one hundred seventy-nine WashAssist modules carried forward with full parity,

p08
00:00:20.593 --> 00:00:23.588
plus sixteen or more new capability areas.

p09
00:00:23.588 --> 00:00:25.581
Say "per the documentation."

p10
00:00:25.581 --> 00:00:29.200
You are quoting it, not claiming you counted.

p11
00:00:29.665 --> 00:00:33.930
If the client is technical, there is a second attributed layer.

p12
00:00:33.930 --> 00:00:36.826
The platform was rebuilt on AWS, with token-based sign-in,

p13
00:00:36.826 --> 00:00:40.687
sessions tied to the device, and rate limiting on the busy screens.

p14
00:00:40.687 --> 00:00:43.346
Again, that is the documentation talking,

p15
00:00:43.346 --> 00:00:45.920
not something you can point to on screen.

p16
00:00:46.418 --> 00:00:50.639
For "what is coming," keep it to what is documented.

p17
00:00:50.639 --> 00:00:55.354
Release two moves Marketing onto an event-driven backbone with two-way data replication.

p18
00:00:55.354 --> 00:00:57.221
Release three brings event-driven microservices.

p19
00:00:57.221 --> 00:00:57.967
No dates.

p20
00:00:57.967 --> 00:01:01.570
If they push for a date, that is parked.

p21
00:01:02.126 --> 00:01:03.967
Now the question you will actually get: where did my feature go.

p22
00:01:04.335 --> 00:01:05.735
Whole modules were regrouped.

p23
00:01:06.252 --> 00:01:07.953
Employees, Gamification, and the Scheduler live under Team now.

p24
00:01:08.165 --> 00:01:11.808
Maintenance, Incidents, and appointment Scheduling are under Operations.

p25
00:01:12.147 --> 00:01:15.846
Mobile and the Portal are under Digital.

p26
00:01:16.053 --> 00:01:18.190
Support and Audit sit under IT and Support.

p27
00:01:18.539 --> 00:01:23.920
And Billing and Academy are brand new.

p28
00:01:24.495 --> 00:01:28.173
Some features did not leave, they just moved or became a button.

p29
00:01:28.713 --> 00:01:31.292
Retention Log is a button on the Customer List.

p30
00:01:31.885 --> 00:01:34.754
Generate Invoices is a button on House Accounts.

p31
00:01:35.301 --> 00:01:37.889
Rewards moved into Settings, under Services.

p32
00:01:38.321 --> 00:01:40.227
Adjustments moved into Inventory.

p33
00:01:40.867 --> 00:01:42.709
Forecasting is under Analytics.

p34
00:01:43.078 --> 00:01:45.086
Report scheduling is on the Reports hub.

p35
00:01:45.610 --> 00:01:51.280
The full map is in our own verified records,

p36
00:01:51.725 --> 00:01:51.905
so you are citing what we saw, not guessing.

p37
00:01:51.905 --> 00:01:53.710
Here is the rule that keeps you honest.

p38
00:01:54.596 --> 00:01:58.619
If you cannot find a feature live, you do not say it is gone.

p39
00:01:59.466 --> 00:02:06.119
PIN Codes, Loyalty Discounts, Tech Commissions, Site Watch,

p40
00:02:06.785 --> 00:02:09.922
and a few others are not visible today.

p41
00:02:10.300 --> 00:02:12.844
The correct answer is that their status is being confirmed.

p42
00:02:13.260 --> 00:02:15.944
It might have moved, it might be in a later release.

p43
00:02:16.400 --> 00:02:16.651
Log the ask, and let it be answered properly.

p44
00:02:16.651 --> 00:02:17.733
So, three moves.

p45
00:02:18.167 --> 00:02:20.350
Give the parity story and attribute it.

p46
00:02:20.804 --> 00:02:23.417
Locate the specific feature from the verified map.

p47
00:02:23.946 --> 00:02:26.448
And never, ever call something gone.

p48
00:02:26.750 --> 00:02:28.880
Confirm first, then answer.

